author: Adam Shear
title: IHSAA releases football sectional pairings
text:
IHSAA releases football sectional pairings Posted: 
The road to the state championships in Indianapolis starts in less than two weeks for local high school football teams. 
Sunday, teams around Indiana found out where their postseason will begin. 
Here's a look at the sectional games coming up for teams in Michiana starting October 23rd. You'll be able to watch highlights of most of these games on FOX28's Sports Extra. 
CLASS 6A (Championships on October 30th) Sectional 2 (4 teams) G1: Warsaw at Carroll (Fort Wayne). G2: Homestead at Fort Wayne Northrop. 
CLASS 5A Sectional 9 (5 teams) - Championship Nov. 6 First Round G1: Elkhart Memorial at South Bend Adams. Oct. 23 Semifinals G2: Michigan City at G1 winner. Oct. 30 G3: Elkhart Central at Mishawaka. Oct. 30 Sectional 10 (4 teams) - Championship Oct. 30 Semifinals G1: Concord at Fort Wayne North Side. G2: Goshen at Fort Wayne Snider. 
CLASS 4A (Championships November 6th) Sectional 18 (8 teams) G1: Kankakee Valley at South Bend Riley. G2: South Bend St. Joseph at Hobart. G3: New Prairie at Andrean. G4: South Bend Washington at South Bend Clay. Semifinals Game 5: G1 winner vs. G2 winner. Game 6: G3 winner vs. G4 winner. Sectional 19 (8 teams) G1: East Noble at NorthWood. G2: Columbia City at Northridge. G3: Wawasee at Plymouth.
